Contributing to two different teams- ‚ÄòTeam Kisan' and ‚ÄòTeam Drishti' was overwhelming but the realization that, through my projects, I could deliver ripple effects in the community- be it in the lives of farmers or differently-abled people, was certainly more promising. A bunch of high-school pass-outs coming together to create impacts on society sounds a bit fancy. [...] 4 2 RELATED WORK 2.1 Visual Storytelling Early works in story visualization have predominantly employed GAN or VAE-based approaches [14, 41, 43, 48, 77]. For example, StoryGAN  pioneered the story visualization task by proposing a GAN-based framework that considers both the full story and the current sentence for coherent image generation. Other early meth-ods adopted a dataset-driven approach, relying on models trained on popular datasets such as PororoSV , FlintstonesSV , or the StorySalon dataset . However, these methods face significant limitations due to the size and quality of existing datasets, making it difficult to generalize to diverse characters, scenes, and cultural contexts.
